      <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><i><b>Summer Wishes, Winter Dreams</b></i> is a <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1973" title="1973">1973</a> film which tells the story of a <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_York_City" title="New York City">New York City</a> homemaker who rethinks her relationships with her husband, her children and her mother. The movie stars <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joanne_Woodward" title="Joanne Woodward">Joanne Woodward</a>, <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Martin_Balsam" title="Martin Balsam">Martin Balsam</a>, <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sylvia_Sidney" title="Sylvia Sidney">Sylvia Sidney</a> and <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Teresa_Hughes&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" title="Teresa Hughes (page does not exist)">Teresa Hughes</a>, was written by <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stewart_Stern" title="Stewart Stern">Stewart Stern</a>, and directed by <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gilbert_Cates" title="Gilbert Cates">Gilbert Cates</a>.</p>
      <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><i>Summer Wishes, Winter Dreams</i> garnered nominations for <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academy_Awards" title="Academy Awards">Academy Awards</a> for <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academy_Award_for_Best_Actress" title="Academy Award for Best Actress">Best Actress in a Leading Role</a> (Joanne Woodward) and <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Academy_Award_for_Best_Supporting_Actress" title="Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress">Best Actress in a Supporting Role</a> (Sylvia Sidney).</p>
